Alberto Soresina (born in Milan, 10 May 1911 and died in 2007) was an Italian musicologist and composer.
Born in Milan in 1911, he studied at the Milan Conservatory and at Accademia Musicale Chigiana in Siena.
He was a professor of singing at the Milan Conservatory and Turin Conservatory (1959-1962), and later composition at the Milan Conservatory.
